  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Jamieson-Fausset-Brown Bible Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "CHAPTER 26",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "1Ch 26:1-12. Divisions of the Porters.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "1, 2. Concerning the divisions of the porters—There were four thousand (1Ch 23:6), all taken from the families of the Kohathites and Merarites (1Ch 26:14), divided into twenty-four courses—as the priests and musicians.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Meshelemiah the son of Kore, of the sons of Asaph—Seven sons of Meshelemiah are mentioned (1Ch 26:2), whereas eighteen are given (1Ch 26:9), but in this latter number his relatives are included.",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
