        "text": "Verses 4, 5.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - Here we have the enumeration of eight sons of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Obed-edom",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Chronicles 15:21, 24",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Chronicles 16:38",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). That in this last reference Obed-edom seems to be called \"son of Jeduthun\" is owing probably to the omission of a name. For former occurrences of the sentence, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "God blessed him",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", with its present evident allusion, see ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Chronicles 13:14",
        "children": []
      },
      {
